.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EYour%20muscles%20can%20shrink.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22space_3%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5aeb50e719ee862c008b47fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESkye%20Gould%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20need%20muscles%20when%20you're%20weightless%2C%20so%20they%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fhrp%2Fbodyinspace%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eatrophy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20absorb%20the%20extra%20tissue.%20This%20is%20why%20physical%20exercise%20is%20a%20part%20of%20every%20astronaut's%20schedule.%20But%20nothing%20seems%20to%20maintain%20muscle%20mass%20better%20than%20the%20strain%20of%20living%20in%20the%20gravity%20found%20at%20Earth's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EYou'll%20be%20sleepy.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22space_2%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5aeb50e719ee8622008b4860%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESkye%20Gould%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou'd%20probably%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-starliner-pilot-butch-wilmore-sleeping-bag-on-the-iss-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep-deprived%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20astronauts%20only%20get%206%20hours%20a%20night%20because%20sleeping%20in%20space%20feels%20weird.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EYour%20cancer%20risk%20increases.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22space_8%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5aeb50e719ee8659008b4856%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESkye%20Gould%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERadiation%20bombarding%20your%20body%20outside%20of%20Earth's%20protective%20magnetic%20field%20can%20increase%20your%20risk%20of%20getting%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20currently%20limits%20astronauts'%20lifetime%20radiation%20exposure%20to%203%2C250%20millisieverts%20for%20males%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmars-radiation-levels-spacex-nasa-exposure-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eequival%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmars-radiation-levels-spacex-nasa-exposure-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eent%20to%20about%20400%20CT%20scans%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20abdomen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFemale%20astronauts%20typically%20have%20more%20tissue%20that's%20susceptible%20to%20radiation%2C%20so%20their%20lifetime%20limit%20is%202%2C500%20mSv.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnimal%20research%20suggests%20this%20threat%20could%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmartian-radiation-levels-crewed-mission-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworse%20in%20deep%20space%20than%20previously%20thought%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20studies%20involving%20humans%20are%20needed%20to%20confirm%20that's%20also%20true%20for%20astronauts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EYour%20genetic%20code%20behaves%20differently.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22genetic-code-behaves-differently-in-space%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5aeb7ab519ee8622008b4877%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESkye%20Gould%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDNA%20is%20life's%20basic%20blueprint%2C%20and%20genes%20%E2%80%94%20much%20like%20words%20in%20a%20cookbook%20%E2%80%94%20spell%20out%20the%20specific%20recipes%20to%20keep%20us%20alive.%20However%2C%20it's%20equally%20important%20when%20and%20how%20much%20those%20genes%20are%20expressed%2C%20or%20turned%20on%20and%20off.%20A%20lot%20of%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20a%20person's%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Twins%20Study%20found%20that%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-twin-study-new-results-mark-scott-kelly-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E7%25%20of%20Scott%20Kelly's%20genes%20expressed%20a%20bit%20differently%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20year%20in%20space%20than%20they%20did%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20didn't%20return%20to%20normal%20(or%20at%20least%20not%20quickly).%20The%20real-world%20ramifications%20of%20this%20are%20still%20being%20explored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20if%20you%20die%20in%20space%3F%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226852%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22space%20walk%20floating%20iss%20astronaut%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F56f02d169105844d018b7ca2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226904%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20has%20ever%20died%20on%20the%20ISS.%20The%20farther%20humans%20travel%20from%20Earth%2C%20however%2C%20and%20the%20longer%20time%20they%20spend%20in%20space%2C%20the%20greater%20the%20risk%20is%20that%20someone%20could%20die%20from%20a%20medical%20event%2C%20a%20vehicle%20emergency%20like%20a%20fire%2C%20depressurization%2C%20electrical%20shock%2C%20or%20simply%20a%20lack%20of%20food%20and%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NASA%2C%20if%20someone%20were%20to%20die%20in%20space%20one%20of%20the%20most%20immediate%20concerns%20would%20be%20how%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20closed%20atmosphere%20of%20a%20space%20vehicle%2C%20the%20natural%20byproducts%20of%20decomposition%20and%2For%20potential%20pathogens%20released%20during%20the%20decomposition%20process%20could%20contaminate%20the%20enclosed%20vehicle%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA%20explains%20in%20a%20technical%20brief%20from%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20crew%20is%20close%20to%20Earth%2C%20like%20on%20the%20ISS%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20options%2C%20NASA%20says%3A%20return%20the%20body%20to%20Earth%2C%20place%20it%20in%20a%20safe%20orbit%20around%20Earth%2C%20or%20allow%20it%20to%20burn%20up%20in%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20final%20decision%20would%20have%20to%20take%20into%20account%20multiple%20factors%20including%20minimizing%20risk%20to%20surviving%20crewmembers%2C%20potential%20forensics%20collection%2C%20biohazard%20containment%2C%20and%20legal%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20crew%20are%20far%20from%20Earth%2C%20like%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20Mars%2C%20the%20option%20is%20to%20either%20try%20to%20preserve%20the%20body%20for%20return%20to%20Earth%20%E2%80%94%20which%20relies%20on%20the%20crew%20being%20able%20to%20handle%20the%20remains%20properly%20%E2%80%94%20or%20jettison%20the%20remains%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-effects-human-body-space%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742411968000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a04e06235876e1b008b5226%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-effects-human-body-space%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Space%20changes%20the%20human%20body%20in%20many%20ways.%20From%20bone%20loss%20to%20bloated%20faces%2C%20here's%20how%20microgravity%20and%20radiation%20affect%20the%20human%20body.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sgould%40businessinsider.com%20(Skye%20Gould%2CDave%20Mosher%2CRebecca%20Harrington%2CMorgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-effects-human-body-space%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Disha%20Salian's%20father%20seeks%2