Survivor%20Gets%20Justice%20From%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUpholding%20a%20man's%20conviction%20in%20a%2039-year-old%20rape%20case%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20commiserated%20with%20the%20woman%20and%20her%20family%2C%20who%20had%20to%20wait%20so%20long%20for%20closure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20great%20sadness%20that%20this%20minor%20girl%20and%20her%20family%20have%20to%20go%20through%20nearly%20four%20decades%20of%20life%2C%20waiting%20to%20close%20this%20horrific%20chapter%20of%20her%2Ftheir%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Vikram%20Nath%20and%20Sanjay%20Karol%2C%20setting%20aside%20the%20Rajasthan%20High%20Court's%20July%202013%20verdict%20acquitting%20the%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%2C%20who%20was%20a%20minor%20in%201986%2C%20was%20raped%20by%20%C2%A0a%2021-year-old%20man.%20In%20November%201987%2C%20he%20was%20convicted%20by%20a%20trial%20court%20and%20given%20a%20seven-year%20jail%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20case%20ran%20the%20gamut%20of%20various%20court-rooms%20till%20it%20ended%20in%20the%20Rajasthan%20High%20Court%2C%20which%20acquitted%20him%20citing%20the%20lack%20of%20strong%20statements%20from%20prosecution%20witnesses%2C%20including%20the%20assaulted%20child.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20child%20witness%20(victim)%2C%20it%20is%20true%2C%20has%20not%20deposed%20anything%20about%20the%20commission%20of%20the%20offence%20against%20her.%20When%20asked%20about%20the%20incident%2C%20the%20trial%20judge%20records%20that%20'V'%20(victim)%20was%20silent%2C%20and%20upon%20being%20further%20asked%2C%20only%20shed%20silent%20tears%20and%20nothing%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20cannot%20be%20counted%20as%20a%20factor%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20the%20judges%20said.%20The%20silence%20of%20the%20child%20had%20stemmed%20from%20the%20trauma.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20silence%20of%20a%20child%20cannot%20be%20equated%20with%20that%20an%20adult%20survivor%2C%20which%20again%20has%20to%20be%20weighed%20in%20its%20own%20circumstances%2C%20the%20judges%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20child%20%26quot%3Btraumatised%20at%20a%20tender%20age%20by%20this%20ghastly%20imposition%20upon%20her%26quot%3B%20cannot%20be%20the%20basis%20on%20which%20the%20accused%20can%20be%20put%20behind%20bars%26quot%3B.%20It%20would%20be%20unfair%20to%20%26quot%3Bburden%20her%20young%20shoulders%20with%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20entire%20prosecution%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judges%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20there%20was%20no%20hard%20and%20fast%20rule%20that%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20condemning%20statement%2C%20a%20conviction%20couldn't%20stand%2C%20particularly%20when%20other%20evidence--medical%20and%20circumstantial--was%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20its%20verdicts%20on%20child%20survivors%20of%20sexual%20assault%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20the%20first%20appellate%20court%2C%20the%20high%20court%20was%20expected%20to%20independently%20assess%20the%20evidence%20before%20confirming%20or%20disturbing%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20court%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20also%20expressed%20surprise%20over%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20high%20court%20dealt%20with%20the%20matter%20and%20frowned%20upon%20the%20survivor%20being%20named%20in%20its%20verdict%20throughout.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20was%20ordered%20to%20surrender%20within%20four%20weeks%20to%20serve%20the%20sentence%20awarded%20by%20the%20trial%20court%2C%20if%20not%20already%20served%2C%20the%20judges%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742410080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F07o74n2_supreme-court_625x300_01_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fafter-40-years-rape-survivor-gets-justice-from-supreme-court-7963208%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Upholding%20a%20m