ons%20that%20have%20considerably%20weakened%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMental%20health%20experts%20suggest%20that%20there%20be%20an%20age%20limit%20for%20children%20who%20undertake%20coaching.%20Children%20as%20young%20as%2014%20and%2015%20are%20also%20taken%20out%20of%20school%20and%20put%20through%20the%20gruelling%20system%20by%20ambitious%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20expected%20that%20the%20bill%20would%20set%20a%20cut-off%20age%20of%20at%20least%2016%20years.%20But%20there%20is%20not%20mention%20of%20this%20in%20the%20version%20that%20was%20tabled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20does%20not%20make%20it%20compulsory%20for%20children%20to%20sit%20for%20an%20aptitude%20test%20before%20enrolling%20for%20coaching%20classes%20for%20medical%20and%20engineering%20entrance%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20draft%20bill%2C%20they%20said%20they%20would%20set%2016%20as%20an%20age%20limit%20for%20admission%20to%20coaching.%20Now%20this%20is%20not%20there%20in%20the%20bill.%20It%20looks%20like%20this%20government%20is%20hand-in-glove%20with%20the%20coaching%20industry.%20The%20industry%20is%20big%20and%20powerful%20and%20this%20is%20a%20racket%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tikaram%20Jully%2C%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20matter%2C%20Prem%20Chand%20Bairwa%2C%20Minister%20for%20technical%20education%2C%20refuted%20the%20allegation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%20we%20have%20simply%20put%20forward%20a%20bill%20to%20regulate%20coaching.%20As%20people%20give%20their%20suggestions%2C%20we%20will%20incorporate%20them%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20holding%20an%20aptitude%20test%20to%20see%20if%20the%20children%20can%20fit%20into%20medical%20and%20engineering%20studies%2C%20the%20minister%20said%20they%20are%20leaving%20this%20option%20for%20parents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20bill%20has%20a%20good%20aim%2C%20but%20it%20is%20a%20bad